description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for an experienced Sonographer band 7 to join the Staff Bank, based at the Queen Alexandra Hospital, Portsmouth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Portsmouth is one of the largest NHS trusts in the country. Joining the Staff Bank as a Sonographer we can offer you a more flexible shift pattern, as well as the opportunities to work across different departments, gaining invaluable skills and experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential Requirements;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Postgraduate Diploma/MSc in Medical Ultrasound (Obstetrics, Gynaecology +/- general ultrasound) or Diploma in Medical Ultrasound or International equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relevant professional registration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain patient confidentiality at all times and adhere to Data Protection Act (Caldicot)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Right to Work in the UK&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Bank Sonographers are invaluable to us and in return for their dedication and commitment, we offer the following benefits:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive pay rates and weekly pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities to work across various departments and sites, gaining invaluable knowledge and experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Priority of shifts over agency workers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An online self-booking system and dedicated bookings team, accommodating your convenience and availability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Electronic Timesheet submission&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Onsite office and designated Business Partners to offer daily support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A professional AHP Recruitment Team that will ensure you are registered and compliant to work shifts as soon as possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dedicated compliance team that will ensure you remain compliant to work, sending out regular expiry updates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We also offer Core Skills Training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please apply directly to this advertisement by submitting you current CV, for further information on the roles please contact the Portsmouth Hospital Staff Bank Team on 0333 577 3316.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
